channel.title: AMP Podcast
channel.description: AMP "Ayaw Mo Paminaw" Podcast is a Bisaya show hosted in the Philippines for Bisaya people and to people who understand the Bisaya language. This podcast primarily focuses on entertainment and learning and various strange theories. Dive deep with us as we explore an endless sea of possibilities and ideas that we love to share with you.

item.title: Ep21 - Am I Real?
item.dc:creator: Ayaw Mo Paminaw
item.description: Are we really living in a Simulation? the Earth, the people will know and meet, the Universe we observe, are these only just an Artificial Simulation? a Computer Simulation? Well, we really don't know yet. Why does this thought even matter? Does knowing the truth would make any difference on how you will live your life? Find out on this Episode about the Simulation Theory, Mandela Effect, Deja Vu, Video Games, Simulation Movies, and MORE.

item.title: Ep19 - Love Languages
item.dc:creator: Ayaw Mo Paminaw
item.description: How do you express your meaningful love to someone? Through touch? Through sweet and flowery words? Through giving gifts, money , time, effort? Join us as we talk about Gary Chapman's book, The 5 Love Languages and the advantages in learning these languages. Does this knowledge can help couples enhance their relationship? Do you really need to learn your partner's love language to develop a healthy and fulfilling relationship?

item.title: Ep18 - #PaWoke: Mulat sa Realidad
item.dc:creator: Ayaw Mo Paminaw
item.description: From the past tense word of "Wake" meaning emerge from a state of sleep but in a sense that they're socially awake or alert on the aspect of the social issues around us. It became a meme phrase, labeling these vocal people with cringey and dissenting opinions, it also became a word for "smart-shaming", discriminating the person while neglecting his/her opinion and argument. Does being PaWoke makes you smart and intellectual that you will be vulnerable for smart-shamers? or Does being PaWoke makes you dumb instead, since you're just creating an issue about almost everything, creating more Drama. Mulat ka na ba talaga? Nakamata na ba jud kaha ka?

item.title: Ep17 - Does Religion causes conflict?
item.dc:creator: Ayaw Mo Paminaw
item.description: Religion teaches humanity about love, understanding and compassion but there are too many different religions with different beliefs that divided humanity causing wars ,conflicts and misunderstanding. As Israel-Palestine conflict rises these days, let's discuss what can we reflect on this as a human. We will also share our thoughts about Filipino Territorial issues, Just War, History of Religion, etc.

item.title: Ep16 - Why is Law of Attraction dumb?
item.dc:creator: Ayaw Mo Paminaw
item.description: Law of Attraction is the belief that positive or negative thoughts bring positive or negative experiences into a person's life. What if we only focus on the negative side like "The results of negative thoughts are always negative consequences." Do you agree that this thinking is ridiculous ? or Do you think this is the best mindset to achieve a successful life. Join us as we question the validity of LOA and we also discuss about Networking, Success, the Purpose Life, Law of Motion, etc. Enjoy this Episode!
